<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="983" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d983">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14108.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 30, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The rupture mentioned in my December 29 was confirmed from Zapatista
                            sources today and details given of the harsh words and drastic action of
                            Villa.</p>
                        <p>It is said the Convention will meet here on January 1 as publicly
                            announced.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>